RIYADH, Oct. 26 (Xinhua) -- The fifth edition of the Future Investment Initiative (FII) commenced on Tuesday in the Saudi capital Riyadh, the Saudi Press Agency reported. Themed "Invest in Humanity," the three-day event attracts more than 2,000 missions and 5,000 company leaders, policymakers, investors and innovators from across the world, aiming to discuss ways to invest in clean water, education, public health, gender equality and fighting poverty. Ghadah Al-Muteiri, a member of the FII Institute Board of Trustees, highlighted the importance of effecting measurable and sustainable growth for future generations in her opening remarks, noting that the FII is committed to human's future and ways that make life safer. Former First Lady of Mozambique Graca Machel made the remarks about artificial intelligence (AI) advancement at one of the event's sessions, noting that despite the AI achievements in different fields, it caused a high unemployment rate. Saudi Minister of Tourism Ahmed Al Khateeb stressed the importance of finding unified global travel regulations and legislation, urging cooperation between countries and the private sector that runs tourism activities. The event is expected to witness the launch of many healthcare, AI, social, environmental and education governance initiatives. Enditem